law.text:
Upon a person's dissociation as a limited partner:
Subject to KRS 362.2-704, the person does not have further rights as a limited partner;
The person's obligation of good faith and fair dealing as a limited partner under KRS 362.2-305(2) continues only as to matters arising and events occurring before the dissociation;
Subject to KRS 362.2-704 and 362.2-951 to 362.2-963, any transferable interest owned by the person in the person's capacity as a limited partner immediately before dissociation is owned by the person as a mere transferee; and
The dissociation does not of itself discharge the person from any obligation to the limited partnership or the other partners which the person incurred while a limited partner.
